Full Description: Barotex Technology Corporation holds an exclusive license agreement to produce and distribute Barotex fibers and fabrics.  Barotex fibers are processed out of mineral rocks of volcanic origin through multiple confidential patented processes. The base fibers formulated with carbon or ceramic fibers and/or various metals have been developed into new hybrid composite type materials and technologies to open a new page in 21st Century fiber material science.  Depending upon the weave and composite material introduced into the fibers, Barotex can work as a replacement for conventional construction and manufacturing materials such as fiberglass, Kevlar, carbon fiber, steel, aluminum and wood in a wide range of applications. Physical properties of Barotex Fiber include high strength, stability, moisture resistance, fire resistance, chemical resistance, electrically non-conductive, and low thermal conductivity. Environmentally Friendly Characteristics include the fact that Barotex fibers are 100% Recyclable, non-petroleum based, sustainable to produce, and creates far less pollution when compared to today's commonly used construction and manufacturing materials.

Description: Barrelhand is creating products that are uniquely designed to meet the requirements of human life in space.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Barrelhand is focused on the challenges that need to be solved to extend human life beyond Earth. Space exploration is on the verge of a new era. Soon, the Artemis program will bring humans back to the moon. Crewed missions to Mars will follow, moving humanity closer to becoming a multi-planetary species. Pushing towards this next frontier, we are deeply curious about the questions that will arise and the transformative potential that will touch the lives of all of us. While there are extreme technological challenges, we will equally be challenged by questions about how to live beyond our home planet. This includes questions of culture, identity, consciousness, and the everyday mundane experience of being human. Barrelhand is exploring these questions by creating products that are uniquely designed to meet the requirements of human life in space. We understand ourselves as a platform for innovation that is open to technologists, scientists and artists who are prepared to bring their insights towards this mission. Our journey started in 2014 with a limited edition timepiece called Project One, which explored and demonstrated the potential of additive manufacturing (3D-printing) for mechanical watchmaking. More than a watch, Project One has been a pioneer and research outlet for an upcoming technology that offers vast, yet largely unrealized potential. At the moment, we are developing our next-generation product line and infrastructure, which will include an array of cutting-edge technologies and insights to meet the harsh requirements of space. We invite everyone to join this journey - whether you are an astronaut flying to space or someone at home looking towards the dreams and promises of the starry night.
